title: Kelce plans to play in '25: 'Can't go out like that'
description: Chiefs tight end Travis Kelce plans to play this season, he said in a text message to Pat McAfee.
author: ESPN

title: Chiefs to franchise tag guard Smith, source says
description: The Chiefs have informed Pro Bowl guard Trey Smith that he will use the franchise tag on him, a source told ESPN's Adam Schefter on Thursday.
author: Adam Teicher

title: 'We are still in the fight' - just how bad does it look for Leicester?
description: Leicester boss Ruud van Nistelrooy insists his side are 'still in the fight' to stay up despite suffering an 11th loss in 12 Premier League games at West Ham.

title: Humphries beats Littler to win Exeter final
description: World number one Luke Humphries defeats world champion Luke Littler 6-4 to win night four of the Premier League in Exeter.

title: Are the glory days for Giannis a thing of the past?
description: The Bucks' two-time MVP Giannis Antetokounmpo finds himself in the unenviable position of chasing not only monstrously productive peers, but his own ghost.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: NFL combine live updates: 40-yard dash begins for DL and LB prospects
description: The 2025 NFL Draft season kicks off as the teams meet the top college prospects at the combine in Indianapolis.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Humphries earns first Premier League win over Littler in Night Four final
description: Luke Humphries earned his first Premier League Darts victory over Luke Littler at the seventh attempt in the Night Four final in Exeter, further stretching his lead at the top of the 2025 table.

title: LaLiga president reveals complaint against Man City filed to EU Commission
description: LaLiga president Javier Tebas says the Spanish league has filed a legal complaint to the EU Commission, alleging that Manchester City have breached EU Competition Law.
